Back in 2016, they rolled out this parody to you with promises that by purchasing the DELUX version you would receive all future additions for FREE. As a result, the community was fucked, and DLC starting with “Rise and Fall” was no longer included in DELUX, all that was left was to buy more. And after that, people, blindly forgetting all the promises of the incompetent developers, continue to smear themselves with this shit and praise it. Your priorities are now clear. However, I believe that the crap in this “town” needs to be shaken up. What's wrong with part six:
1. The game had spyware, and it still does. In the end, everyone unanimously forgot this topic, although it was vigorously discussed back in 17-18;
2.) AI on difficulty higher than “Prince” simply receives a damage bonus against the player and additional units for development, and the player receives a penalty to the bot’s attack. Bots always hate you, under any circumstances, their demands are absolutely stupid due to national ideas and the whims of the leader. And this despite the fact that the development of your civilization will slow down due to complexity, so it will be virtually impossible to avoid hatred. On difficulty below "Prince" the AI is just as stupid, but it develops more slowly and its attitude towards you is warmer. The AI is not developed from the word “AT ALL”: you are either hated or inferior to you, but they will hate you more often, and on high difficulty - always. The strength of the AI lies not in tactics, but in the fact that at the beginning it receives a second settler, two detachments of workers, more troops and bonuses to damage against the player, and maybe even bonuses for the palace in the city. This is the same as making enemies 100% fatter in a shooter and doubling their damage. It won’t make the game more interesting, it will only make the killing process longer. The developers are not much smarter than the AI itself if they couldn’t come up with a good implementation for it. For an example of good bots: AI in "Age of Empires II";
3.) The mediocre branch of “Technology” and “Culture”. In the fifth part, the process of development of culture and science was simpler, without any stupid thoughts about connections with the regions (regions are a completely different topic, it’s just fucked up). Technologies are scattered everywhere and often without any connection with the previous one; for some reason you can’t download some technologies and forget about them. The same goes for culture. Eureka and inspiration? The innovation may indeed be interesting, but what to do if there are no barbarians on the map? Will I have to spend a ton of moves to unlock bronze processing? The eureka system has not been fully thought through. As a result, one player will appear on an island where it is actually impossible to get either eureka from barbarians or inspiration from city-states, and the other will receive all these pies and fly to a higher technology and institute. Well, one more important point: as soon as you open the so-called “At-Arms”, in a few moves you will be able to get “Musketeers”, although there should be ARQUEBUSERS first, because they appeared earlier, motherfucker, and “Musketeers” were with XVI century, when firearms were already in use. Why the hell are these “Latniks” needed when they are already virtually obsolete after just one technology? There are no arquebusiers in the game, and the "Field Cannon" can only be upgraded to the "Machine Gun Company". And it’s all about the distance from the opening of the “Field Gun” to the “Machine Gun Company”. This distance is unreasonably huge, it is even greater than in the fifth part. I highly doubt that cannonballs were still in use at the end of the 19th century. Moreover, this gun doesn’t even really do damage to the “Line Infantry”, which also opens VERY soon after the “Musketeers”. And doubts regarding operation are not at all false, because at the end of the 19th century, 75< caliber artillery pieces were already invented. Then why the hell are artillery installations only unlocked with TANKS, WHEN THEY WERE USED BEFORE THE FIRST WORLD WAR?! Is it really so difficult to go to at least WIKIPEDIA and see for yourself? And no one cares that back in “Antiquity” and “The Middle Ages” wagons were used to supply the army, but for some reason it opens only in “Modern Time”. Apparently there were no field orderlies in the “Middle Ages” either; the developers know everything better than anyone. And in the game there are no: mortars, tanks and WWI assault infantry, anti-tank guns, PanzerSHREK and all civilizations have Shermans, when for such a price tag it was possible to make each civilization its own unique tank. They made swordsmen, why not make armored vehicles? And there is also incredibly little technology;
4.) The most miserable builder system in the entire history of the series. I will never understand the joy of spamming workers and wasting moves creating them. THEY STILL DON'T KNOW how to make roads. And to make roads, you need CARAVANS, and to have more than one caravan, you need to make COMMERCE CENTERS, but it will be bad if there are no other areas or other shit nearby. It’s hard to even comment on this, because the blazing ass can be seen from a distance of 30 km. But for some reason, A MILITARY ENGINEER CAN BUILD ROADS. Apparently you have to be a military man to do this. What kind of developers are all such bastards. At the same time, he has TWO CHARGES and HE SPENDS CHARGES on one square of the road
